If you know me, you know I LOVE a good collaboration...and let me tell you, this one, especially, is SO GOOD! The oh so lovely folks over at Canadian based (and soon in Australia!) @seagodssup asked if I would create a design for their best all around board, the Diatom (their biggest and widest board, fantastic for beginners and fun for all levels!). As you can guess, it was an easy YES! It was quite a bit of teamwork over the last month to get this just right, but we are so thrilled with the results and can't wait to see them out on waters all over the world! 

They are taking orders for presale right now and are offering a killer price on this beauty! If you are in the market for a SUP, I can't recommend this company enough, the owners Mandy and Ryan are top notch humans who truly support independent artists and important causes. Swipe through to check out the mock up…it’s being made right now and I will soon share photos of the actual board! ❤️ #sup #seagodssup #mandala #standuppaddleboard #collboration #getoutonthewater #supyoga #artistsoninstagram #shopsmall

A bit of the process creating the design for the 2023 @seagodssup Diatom! So many iterations of this design…even before I sent it off for the first draft round! When it comes to printing my work, I’ve had a few redo’s to simplify my designs…but not this time! My first round was somewhat bare bones compared to this design so when they returned feedback and wanted MORE detail, I was like ooooh yes! let. me. at. it!
I’ve been meaning to make cookie press designs for so long…so I gave one of my mandala ornaments from last year a go and love the results! Makes me want to make proper ones for next year!

“When women gather in circles with one another, the world heals a little more.”

I’ve been honored and privileged to gather with these women for over 20 years in mothering, in song and dance, in life transitions, in grief, in support, in co-creating, in silence, in speaking out, in laughter…this way of being with each other, witnessing each other and loving each other is an incredible gift that none of us take for granted. 

We spent an entire weekend celebrating our sisterhood eating amazing food, creating beautiful things, laughing our asses off, and witnessing each other do brave things…and it was glorious. 

As part of our retreat weekend, I managed to convince these amazing women to jump into a recycling bin (because the poorly cold plunge tub I brought decided it couldn’t match the strength of these warriors!) filled with cold water as part of our time together and let me tell you…I am in even more awe of the beauty, grace, courage and tenacity in these women...which of course tracks as that’s what I’ve witnessed in them all the last 20+ years! 

I am so damn lucky…and so infinitely grateful. #womengathering #circleup #create #coldplunge #myfamily #iambecauseweare

Last year, a friend and collector of my work experienced a tragic house fire, in which she not only lost all her belongings, but devastatingly, her two dogs and cat. 💔 Shortly after the fire, her dear friend Misty wrote to tell me that one of the things Ruth was sad to lose, besides her pets of course, was all my work she had collected over the years.  So, while Ruth is in the process of having her house rebuilt, Misty got to planning with me to commission a 3’ x 3’ mandala to gift her dear friend so that when the house is ready, she’ll have artwork that not only symbolizes new beginnings while honoring all that was lost, but also the deep connection, love and friendship these two share…something a fire can never destroy.  #loveenduresall #mandala #carvedmandala #loss #newbeginnings #friendshipgoals #artist #jamielockeart

Another episode of “Things I’ve wanted to create and finally made time for it.” Stepping foot into the world of 3D art…how satisfying and fun! And a bit trippy too! Diving into the captivating world of 3D mandalas has been an incredibly exhilarating journey! Designing in three dimensions has stretched my imagination and pushed the boundaries of my artistic skills, unlocking a whole new dimension of creativity.

From sketching the initial concept to bringing it to life with depth and dimension, every step has challenged and inspired me, allowing me to explore new perspectives and techniques along the way. The sheer delight of seeing this 12 layer mandala come together has fueled my passion for this art form and deepened my love for the creative process. ✨❤️🎉

From the humble beginnings of my first digital mandala 11 years ago (before I started carving them!) to the awe-inspiring design for @seagodssup that I created this year…it’s been a remarkable journey of passion and perseverance!  It serves as a powerful reminder that when we persist in pursuing what ignites our souls, the universe rewards us with extraordinary opportunities and growth. Each intricate pattern and vibrant color in these designs represents countless hours of dedication, experimentation, and unwavering belief in the creative process. It is a testament to the transformative power of following our passions, as we witness the evolution of artistry and the manifestation of dreams. 

I hope this inspires you to never give up on what you love, for if you stay true to your calling, the path will reveal itself and lead you to the most extraordinary destinations! #keepcreating #perserverance #passion #dowhatyoulove #mandalaartist

When @snugin.us asked if I could create an art piece using their Seasons Wheel graphic designed by the talented crew at @guideandanchor, I knew exactly how I wanted to bring it to life! As some of you know, I’ve been diving into some 3D work with my mandalas and thought this design would lend itself beautifully to this method! The result required a little over 120 hours and 4 layers of Baltic Birch to create! I loved, loved working on this piece and I love that it now lives in its home at The Snug, which opens its doors at 3pm today! I have several other works that I had the privilege to create in this stunning pub that I will share over the next week…but trust me, you’ll want to see this amazing space in person so go, enjoy, support local…Sláinte!
